content_vision: I love you. Our love is difficult to maintain. You are such an despiseful bitch. It's all her fault, but she keeps making it worse because I can't fix it. Then she blames me.
text:
Intro:
i can't control myself, she's my addiction,
and all she wanna do is shine bright, flick that switch on.

Verse 1:
i'll treat you so good, girl, i'll make you see,
champagne popping, all over the room, we'll be so carefree.
all this ice around my neck, i feel like an iceberg,
we're just one big family, but we're still blowing ls, having a good time, leaving the haters in the dirt.
why you moving so slow, like you can't keep up the pace,
can't you see, girl, i'm the one who can keep you safe,
our bond so strong, you can always trust in my embrace.
i can't control myself when you're around,

Pre-Chorus 1:
are you a simple woman, just searching for love and truth?
let me show you the light, i swear you won't be missin' nothin' in your youth.

Chorus 1:
take a hit of this bubble kush, feel it in your bones,
and damn, you're like no other, let's make it known.
and they said go snoop, ain't no one gonna stop us, we're in the zone.
girl, i'm not done, don't walk away yet,

Verse 2:
it was pouring there first, my heart was in despair
but with every storm, there's always lessons learned, memories we'll share
thoughts pullin' on my brain, weighing me down like an anchor.
she's caught up in the moment, just wanna let go,
so much to discover, so much of herself to show.
feelin' like heaven when we come together,
you promised me you'd always be my forever,
flying too high, not afraid to fall, 'cause you catch me every time when i give you my all.

Pre-Chorus 2:
if the darkness holds your love inside,
then at least leave me with what you once provided.

Chorus 2:
gotta stand on my own two, no more shading the truth,
when the high wears off, back to reality, gotta face the proof.
i see the pain behind those beautiful eyes,
tell a nigga what you going through, don't hide,

Bridge:
tryna knock me down, but i stay on my feet,
with no room for games, no funny business can be beat.
amour, amour, my love, can't you see,
they tryna bring us down but they'll never stop me.

Outro:
they know it's the place to be, where we all come together
to get our lives right and bond like family, there's nothing better.

Instrumental:
living in nice homes, champagne toasts in the morning,
and we swervin' through these streets, no one can stop our soaring.

down south, we don't take kindly to your jive,

inside my heart, fuck your friendship, i'll see you later.

Intro:
dropping stacks, living lavish, i'm always spendin',
but when that beat drops, we gotta wheel it back and start reppin'.

Verse 1:
people always gotta keep themselves occupied,
gossiping about who got shot and lied,
but i just do me, my bitch do the most.
i ain't about to let my boys die,
give me some time and i'll make the right choice, no lie.
so maybe you should shut your mouth,
look how it worked out, i made it without your doubt.
money keeps rolling in, by the shit load,

Pre-Chorus 1:
she got caught up in a mess, got herself slewed,
but she's still saying 'senorita', you know all about it?

Chorus 1:
if you wanna enter my world, bring some green,
and all i wanna do is show you what you've never seen.
life is hard, it can be rough, it's true,
but je la vie, let's make the moments count,

Verse 2:
all i'm feeling this time of year,
we are drugs, we turn up without any fear.
tin tin tin tin tin tin tin, sound of my flow,
treacherous streets, but i still gotta go.
i ain't trying to be fake, just keeping it real up front,
i keep thinking maybe i should just open up, be honest, and not play the dense part.
i've seen the tears fall, heard the cries,
now i'm ready to step out into the night, taking control of my own life.

Pre-Chorus 2:
my name is lyrics, i'll never steer you wrong,
got that contra flow, just listen to my song.

Chorus 2:
our love is bright and bold, like a bumblebee in flight,
but we can't stay, gotta hit the road tonight.
all these englishmen going insane,
but you, my love, you took me back again,

Bridge:
gotta put my time in, can't just linger,
all of these bank dollars, gotta be a go- getter.
all the guys found a better way to move on,
this is my last line of defense,

Outro:
got some homies in the back, bumping beats,
probably running up a tab, fifteen drinks deep.

Instrumental:
he can't get no money 'cause he don't live right,
but you wanna come around and start another fight,

Intro:
out of nowhere, shorty hit me up on facetime,
and as we unravel each other's truths, we can hear the pain in the distance, where it cries.

Verse 1:
nice homes and fancy cars, that's just the start of it all,
when we reach the top, we'll never have to fall.
my mind is twisted and filled with rage,
and yet you keep me captive, trapped in your orbit like a cage,
but i'm still fresh as peppermint, through all the chaos that encages.
ls, holding it down with a vengeance,
you did me wrong, but i'll make you pay the price for your pretense.
i need to break free, i'm trapped inside my own head,

Pre-Chorus 1:
with these bad bitches, my pockets stay thick,
got mike will on the track, this beat sure to stick.

Chorus 1:
with money pouring in, there's nothing we can't do,
keep trying and we'll make it, our love will stay true.
with money coming by the shit load, we can't see the sky,
but you knew i was coming back, our love will never die.

Verse 2:
cash flowin' in, we're living in luxury,
but if we wanna stay, we gotta make some decisions, you and me.
i'll make her feel the heat, take her to the afterlife,
while the babies cry, but no one hears their strife.
don't care what the haters say,
i just wanna do my thing right now, while i got these gems on my hand.
better shoot that girl, she's got me fuming,
and let me know if we need to start a feud in.

Chorus:
i'm the money boy, no one can deny
they may be lying, but i'm living so fly.
there's an issue at grant, we can't deny
gonna play society, make changes and try.

Verse 1:
now lift them up, all the girls in the club,
who wants drama? we can serve it up.
we them, gotta rep our squad with pride,
were not always eye to eye, but we ride together and thrive.
see the sunrise, another day has come and gone,
and like most, i can't help but feel alone.
i never had my time to shine,
but they can't hold me back, i got plenty of time.

Pre-Chorus 1:
living fast and crazy, we on a different level,
keep switching them girls, we don't like to settle.

Chorus 1:
i can't take this pain anymore, just execute me,
but you won't forget her, she'll always haunt you, see.
they used to say love was just a game,
but now you know they all sentimental now.

Verse 2:
let's escape reality, leave our troubles behind,
dreams are our sanctuary, let's just unwind,
but don't forget, we gotta keep pushing on.
look at my pockets, filled with nothing but emptiness,
and the future looks bleak, no happiness.
let's escape reality, leave our troubles behind,
dreams are our sanctuary, let's just unwind,
but don't forget, we gotta keep pushing on.

Pre-Chorus 2:
up now lyrics, let me get loud,
look how it worked out, i'm just a southern crowd.

Chorus 2:
my homie trying to plant his seed,
you better light that fire, fulfill our needs.
it should be about us, no one else, indeed.
my love for you is like a bright, buzzing yellow bumblebee,

Bridge:
and baby, i know that money can't buy me love,
but i heard of a place at the back of town, a hidden cove.
who really had my back when i was down?
so many helped me rise, now we're taking flight.

Outro:
life is short, gotta seize the day,
with cash flowin' in like a flood, we'll make it anyway
